Project Architecture: main.cpp

This file lists all functions in the project and what each one does.
Order follows the source file.

1) Smoke and Utility Rendering

- initSmoke()
  Initializes the smoke particle pool by marking all particles inactive.

- spawnSmoke(float x, float y, float z)
  Activates one free smoke particle near the given location with random velocity/size/alpha.

- updateSmoke()
  Advances active smoke particles over time (movement, growth, fade-out, deactivation).

- drawSmoke()
  Renders all active smoke particles as blended translucent spheres.

- drawBresenhamLine(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2)
  Draws a 2D line using Bresenham's algorithm via GL points.

- plotCirclePoints(int xc, int yc, int x, int y)
  Plots 8-way symmetric points for midpoint-circle drawing.

- drawMidpointCircle(int xc, int yc, int radius)
  Draws a circle perimeter using midpoint circle algorithm.

- drawMidpointCircleFilled(int xc, int yc, int radius)
  Draws a filled circle by repeatedly drawing midpoint-circle rings.

- drawSunMidpoint(int centerX, int centerY, float visibility)
  Draws stylized 2D sun rays and glow rings on the background UI projection.

- drawRocketTrail()
  Draws a layered white/gray 2D ascent trail behind the rocket during LAUNCHING.

2) Planet Rendering

- drawEarth()
  Draws procedural Earth sphere (ocean/land shading + cloud shell) during CRUISING_TO_MARS.
  Earth now rotates with tilt/spin transform.

- loadMarsBMP(const char *filename, bool &ok)
  Loads a 24-bit uncompressed BMP into an OpenGL texture and returns texture ID.

- setProceduralMarsColor(float nx, float ny, float nz)
  Computes fallback Mars-like color (bands, crater noise, canyon-like dark region, polar brightening).

- drawMarsSphere(float r, int slices, int stacks)
  Draws high-resolution Mars sphere with texture if available, otherwise procedural fallback color.

- drawMars()
  Renders rotating rounded Mars planet during CRUISING_TO_MARS.

- drawStars()
  Renders random star field points in space during CRUISING_TO_MARS.

3) Sky and Terrain Systems

- drawSkyBackground()
  Draws the background sky gradient/sun depending on mission state and altitude.

Earth terrain helpers:
- earthHash2(float x, float y)
  Hash/noise primitive for Earth terrain.

- earthValueNoise(float x, float y)
  Bilinear-smoothed value noise sample.

- earthFbm(float x, float y)
  Multi-octave fractal noise for terrain variation.

- earthGroundHeight(float x, float z)
  Height function for Earth ground undulation.

- earthCrackMask(float x, float z)
  Crack intensity mask to darken dry cracked areas.

- drawEarthGroundSkyGradient()
  Draws Earth-ground scene sky gradient plane.

- drawEarthGroundCloudBands()
  Draws translucent cloud layers.

- drawEarthGroundMountainsDetailed()
  Draws stylized mountain ranges for Earth terrain scene.

- drawEarthGroundDetailed(int size, int step)
  Draws detailed Earth ground mesh with cracks/noise color modulation.

- drawEarthGroundRocks(const std::vector<EarthRock> &group)
  Draws one Earth rock group (far/mid/near).

- drawEarthGroundTwigs()
  Draws twig/debris line segments on Earth ground.

- initEarthGroundScatter()
  Generates random Earth rock/twig scatter datasets.

Mars terrain helpers:
- marsHash2(float x, float y)
  Hash/noise primitive for Mars terrain.

- marsNoise2(float x, float y)
  Bilinear-smoothed value noise sample.

- marsFbm(float x, float y)
  Multi-octave fractal noise for Mars terrain variation.

- marsTerrainHeight(float x, float z)
  Height function for Mars terrain.

- drawMarsGroundSky()
  Draws Mars atmospheric color backdrop.

- drawMarsGroundMountains()
  Draws layered Mars mountain ridges.

- drawMarsGroundDetailed(int size, int step)
  Draws Mars ground mesh with red/orange palette and erosion lines.

- drawMarsGroundRocks()
  Draws all Mars rocks.

- initMarsGroundRocks()
  Randomly generates Mars rock field and per-rock scale/rotation/tone.

- setupMarsGroundFog()
  Enables and configures Mars fog color/range.

- drawGround()
  Central ground router:
  - ARRIVED_MARS: draws Mars sky/mountains/terrain/rocks and fog.
  - Other visible states: draws Earth terrain package.

4) Launch Site and Spacecraft Geometry

- drawLaunchPad()
  Draws launch pad structure (petals, center platform, mount) for non-space/non-Mars states.

- drawLaunchTower()
  Draws service tower and arm near rocket while still on launch site.

- drawDispatchInstruments()
  Draws mission control/dispatch instrument props near launch site.

- drawShuttleOrbiter()
  Draws main rocket body; positions it by state:
  - launch stack position,
  - transfer trajectory in space,
  - Mars landing position anchored to terrain.

- drawSolidRocketBoosters()
  Draws side boosters while attached and applicable to state.

- drawExternalTank()
  Draws external tank while attached and applicable to state.

- drawMainEngineFlames()
  Draws main engine flame triangles during launch.

- drawSRBFlames()
  Draws booster flame triangles during launch before booster separation.

- drawLadder(float x, float bottomY, float topY, float z)
  Draws a ladder model from rails + rungs.

- drawRocketLadders()
  Draws launch ladder when astronaut is still boarding phase.

- drawAstronaut()
  Draws astronaut model and adjusts Mars draw height to terrain when outside rocket.

5) Splash Screen and UI

- drawBitmapText(const char *text, float x, float y, void *font)
  Draws text via GLUT bitmap font at 2D position.

- getTextWidth(const char *text, void *font)
  Computes pixel width of bitmap text.

- drawCenteredText(const char *text, float y, void *font)
  Draws centered text line on splash/UI.

- drawSplashScreen()
  Draws initial splash/intro screen and controls.

- drawButton(Button *btn)
  Draws interactive button with hover color effect.

- drawStatusText()
  Draws mission status/altitude/instruction overlay text.

6) Effects and Mars End Scene Props

- drawExplosion(float x, float y, float z)
  Draws animated mission-failure explosion visuals.

- drawMarsDust()
  Draws landing dust clouds after Mars touchdown.

- drawBangladeshFlag()
  Draws planted Bangladesh flag on Mars terrain after planting completes.

7) Main Render and Input/State Loop

- display()
  Main render function. Sets projection/camera by state, applies lighting/fog choices,
  then draws environment, vehicle, effects, UI, and buttons.

- isMouseOverButton(Button *btn, int mouseX, int mouseY)
  Hit-test utility for button clicks/hover.

- mouse(int button, int state, int x, int y)
  Handles click actions (launch, separation controls, reset) and mission state changes.

- mouseMotion(int x, int y)
  Updates button hover states.

- keyboard(unsigned char key, int x, int y)
  Handles key controls (ESC exit, leave splash screen).

- timer(int value)
  Per-frame simulation update:
  - updates animation clocks (earth/mars rotation, exhaust/smoke)
  - updates mission state machine (launch, cruise, Mars arrival/landing, astronaut walk, flag planting)
  - triggers particle updates and next frame timer.

8) Window/GL Setup

- reshape(int w, int h)
  Updates viewport and projection matrix on window resize.

- init()
  Initializes random seed, OpenGL state/light, textures, particles, Earth/Mars scatter data.

- main(int argc, char **argv)
  Application entry point: creates GLUT window, registers callbacks, prints controls, starts main loop.


Main File Functionality (Step-by-Step, Short)

1. Program starts in main(), initializes GLUT window/context, then calls init().
2. init() configures OpenGL/light, loads Mars texture if available, and prebuilds particle/terrain scatter data.
3. Application enters GLUT event loop (glutMainLoop).
4. display() renders each frame according to mission state:
   splash -> launch scene -> space cruise -> Mars landing scene.
5. timer() advances all simulation states and animations every ~16ms.
6. mouse()/keyboard() accept user actions (launch, staging, reset, splash continue, exit).
7. On Mars end phase, astronaut descends, walks, plants flag; final flag appears on terrain.
